      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "boundary",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Boundary at which to pause speech. The supported bound types are listed in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspeechboundary"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Pass the constant "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspeechboundary/nsspeechimmediateboundary"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to pause immediately, even in the middle of a word. Pass "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspeechboundary/nsspeechwordboundary"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " or "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspeechboundary/nsspeechsentenceboundary"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to pause speech at the end of the current word or sentence, respectively."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can determine whether your application has paused a synthesizer's speech output by obtaining the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspeechstatusproperty"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property through the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspeechsynthesizer/1448436-objectforproperty"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method. While a synthesizer is paused, the speech status information indicates that "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspeechstatusoutputbusy"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspeechstatusoutputpaused"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " are both "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If the end of the string being spoken is reached before the specified pause point, speech output pauses at the end of the string."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
